    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hard ovoid-shaped drupes (stone fruit) of the coconut palm (Cocos nucifera) native to the tropics. Coconuts have a fibrous outer husk and a woody inner shell that contains the coconut meat and white juice. Coconut shells range in diameter from 8 to 14 inches. Despite its name, the coconut is not classified as a nut.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
